<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Yup HoH South Shrine bar none.
<br />
It'll be tough at first with no AA's - trust me I know - but they'll start flying by in no time and it gets easier.  If you find yourself running LoM a lot bring along a druid to snare/harmony for ya.  It will save you from Pacificationing (?) and makes charm/charm breaks sooo much easier.
<br />

<br />
I like to keep my pet around for awhile by mez/memblurring when he gets low on health.  It save mana from having to rehaste and also the little bit of downtime while you wait for blur to kick in allows you to regen a bit.  If he starts getting gay and breaking charm every few seconds I'll get a new one.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
